-- Holder Deciding Whether to Stay on as Attorney General
-- B y   P h i l   M a t t i n g l y
-- 2012-11-08T18:05:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-08/holder-deciding-whether-to-stay-on-as-attorney-general.html
U.S. Attorney General Eric Holder
said he is deciding whether to remain the nation’s top
law enforcement official in President Barack Obama’s second
term.  Holder, speaking today at University of Baltimore School of
Law, said he wants to have a discussion with his family and
Obama, as well as consider what he can accomplish if he stays,
according to  Tracy Schmaler , a Justice Department spokeswoman.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Phil Mattingly in Washington at 
